{"TopicId":138427,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"UI Scaling","CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T05:24:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T05:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new User interface tweaking is great!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TSQhiyU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/TSQhiyU.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly unknown is Map Filter Scale.\u00A0 What it does I cannot find.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso the Part Action Menus should also have scaling option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T05:27:47Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 05:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MoeslyArmlis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T10:56:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed, these feature are excellent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s needed now are KSPedia pages that explain what everything does in the various \u0027settings\u0027 menus, and maybe tooltips that appear when hovering over the slider bars and tick boxes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T11:08:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFYI \u0022Map Filter\u0022 is that gray thing on the top of Map View that turns on and off different kinds of ships.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RW-1","CreatedById":107278,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T14:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesomeness!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m now just trying to find the right combination of sizes and positioning ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and \u002BMoeslyArmlis, got a spare bag of Plutonium Nyborg? \u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T14:48:42Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 02:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by RW-1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nikolai","CreatedById":23085,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T15:11:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222547892\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138427\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461928121\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110905\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brainlord Mesomorph\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Brainlord Mesomorph said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup -- this is something a lot of people wanted, including myself. \u00A0It might be, though, that the kluge they had to make with Unity 4 and the UI in versions prior to 1.1 would have made this impossible or exceedingly difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegardless, I\u0027m very happy to see it. \u00A0I like the idea of various parts being only as intrusive as I want them to be for different missions (and different phases within a single mission).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T18:07:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138427\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461942706\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002223085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nikolai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nikolai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I like the idea of various parts being only as intrusive as I want them to be for different missions (and different phases within a single mission).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndidn\u0027t think of that. I was just happy to get the navball out of the way of the landing shadow,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T18:14:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138427\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461942706\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002223085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nikolai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Nikolai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup -- this is something a lot of people wanted, including myself. \u00A0It might be, though, that the kluge they had to make with Unity 4 and the UI in versions prior to 1.1 would have made this impossible or exceedingly difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegardless, I\u0027m very happy to see it. \u00A0I like the idea of various parts being only as intrusive as I want them to be for different missions (and different phases within a single mission).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/46454-10-enhanced-navball-13/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EEnhanced NavBall\u003C/a\u003E has been doing it forever so I don\u0027t think so.\u00A0 I think it\u0027s just more likely it was on the back burner and when they resized the NavBall to be more console friendly it became an issue and thrust to the front burner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moesly_Armlis","CreatedById":112247,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T23:29:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138427\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461941203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107278\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RW-1\u0022\u003E